What does a media platform look like in web3? 
First, it needs to be centered around XR content. VR and AR are soon going to be primary media consumption devices, so a new media platform should serve these devices from day 1.

Second, it should use blockchain technology to give ownership of that content back to the creators. 

Finally, it should realize that the distance between media and shopping is closing, so it should include the ability to buy and sell both digital and physical items.

That’s what we believe, and that’s what we are creating at Augmio. Augmio is a media platform built for web3. We distribute interactive augmented reality experiences, like a Youtube for AR. We use fractional NFTs to give content ownership to the creator, and allow them to sell partial ownership of their content to their fans. We have an integrated NFT marketplace to visualize, buy, and list NFTs in stunning augmented reality. We’re a small, experienced team and we’re ready to move fast. 

Welcome to Augmio 😊 Currently looking for early investors
https://augmio.com/

Hiya great community. I am not yet ready to formally present our DAO NFT (but that will be very shortly), but I can give you a quick preview, as it seeks to do much of what you are also doing, so many ways to collaborate here
Our DAO has a specific purpose, to take on Big Tech, i.e. "The Social Dilemma Problem"
or, basically converting web 2.0 into web 3.0

Our DAO is comprised of two technology platforms to start, but seeks to add more as the DAO is the community of artists and designers who sell their copyright as  a way to raise resources and awareness to any project that takes on this issue.
Inclusive in this issue is Digital Governance as well (any kind)
Our DAO presents an actionable business plan which both forms the DAO and initiates the business plan, through a series of nine levels of NFT Game Play which fund nine levels of the DAO business plan
By Level 5, our DAO becomes a content broadcast network, reaching millions of internet users, broadcasting the DAO message, which is taking on big tech, to simplify.

Our DAO is a sophisticated economy and business plan, applying specific design principles in its construction that, so far, have. been able to work within US securities law while also finding a pathway to assign equity and profit margin back to our DAO
and every step of the way, members of our DAO make money when they raise money for the DAO, at the exact moment.
We've spent $700k in research as well as piloting and coding, so years of work and investment has already gone into this, so we are starting with something actionable, immediately adoptable.
The name of our DAO is Big Mother
Where as Big Brother is watching you, tracking you, Big Mother is watching out for you 🙂
Thanks for hearing me out on my #🤑shill 🙂
PS: Our DAO generates profit and revenue and equity all within first year

Hi all, I am contributing to a project on the intersection of NFTs DAOs and Writing. Among other things I am creating the early documentation for it, and would love ya'lls feedback. Be brutally honest 😉 

TLDR: 
Time Writer - A creative social experiment to rewrite history and predict the future. Collaborative writing of an infinite story expanding forever into the past and the future.

To ensure that a creative and valuable story will develop, we will utilize silent NFT auctions as submissions for story line proposals. A DAO with existing winners will vote on the submissions, and choose a winner based on which story will best continue the timeline. Every NFT holder will be a DAO member, can vote, and receives a distribution of the winning bids proceeds. 

More info: https://badmonky.notion.site/Time-Writer-Wiki-5afb9765d4da4b22b03be3c7858985e1
